description:
'''Space rock''' is a music genre characterized by loose and lengthy song structures centered on instrumental [[Texture (music)|textures]] that typically produce a [[hypnotic]], otherworldly sound. It may feature [[Distortion (music)|distorted]] and [[reverberation]]-laden guitars, minimal drumming, languid vocals, [[synthesizer]]s, and lyrical themes of [[outer space]] and [[science fiction]].

The genre emerged in late 1960s [[psychedelia]] and [[progressive rock]] bands such as [[Pink Floyd]], [[Hawkwind]], and [[Gong (band)|Gong]] who explored a "cosmic" sound. Similar sounds were pursued in the early 1970s' West German ''[[kosmische Musik]]'' ("cosmic music") scene. By the 1980s and 1990s, the "[[Drone (music)|drone]]-heavy" sound of [[Spacemen 3]], spearheaded a revival of the genre which later influenced [[shoegaze]] and [[post-rock]].

